Vheadline
p2
VReaching new heights
p3
sVnews
p4
VNada Bharathi, in association with Samaja Sampradaya Sangita Niketan, recently started a monthly music concert to promote classical music in the city by coming up with a concept called &#8216;Music at Doorsteps&#8217;. Samaja, a sampradayik classical music training institute run by vocalist Jayapradha, has taken the initiative to propagate music with the help of Nada Bharathi.A flute recital by Nagaraju, a staff artiste of AIR, Hyderabad, was featured. A disciple of renowned vidwan Manda Balarama Sharma, Nagaraju has tremendous experience and rich &#8216;sruthi suddhata&#8217; and &#8216;ghanam&#8217; in his playing.Nagaraju began his recital with a melodious SriragavarnamSami ninne. The varnam was elaborated in a steady way with rich ragam bhavam and kalapramanam. Hamsadwani was taken for a bright ragam wherein he tookAbhista varadhewith rhyming swaram.Ganamurty Sree Krishna Venuin Ganamurty ragam of Thyagaraja was played in a melodious fashion.Sreerama padamin Amritha vahini, another noted Thyagaraja number, came next.Kalyani was taken for a detailed essay. Nagaraju showed his classicism in the ragam, discovering the nuances of the ragam and touching new heights in it. He chose Syamasastry&#8217;sBiranavaralichhiin Tisranadia with good swarakalpana combinations.Brochevaruin Khamas was neatly played with clarity in the sahityam.The main attraction was Khambhoji. The artiste played the ragam in detail with all the rich sangathis finding their way in it. Deekshitar&#8217;sMarakatha valliin adi in the chowkakalam was played to perfection.The nerval was attractive with strong sarvalaghu swaram.Nagaraju concluded his recital withChinnam chirulikiye, a ragamalika of Subramanya Bharathiyar. A Dhanasri thillana was the concluding item of the scintillating recital.
